review_blob: Pours a dark purple. Very grape, sweet nose. Very Cabernet forward flavor with a bittersweet finish. Very nice mead!
Pours gold with a nose full of floral grapes. Sweet flavor that has a sticky sweetness from the honey and grapes. Slight alcohol burn, but a very nice mead.
beer_name: Superstition Snow on Mount Olympus Pyment

review_blob: Pours a dark brown with beautiful sour cherry notes in the nose with an ever so subtle bourbon scent. The sour cherries and plums come through in the flavor. A beautiful sour!
beer_name: Wicked Weed Black Angel Cherry Sour

review_blob: Pours an opaque purple. Fruity berry nose with honey. Tastes similar to the nose. Very nice blend of berries, raspberry and blackberry. Really like this mead, but the sparkling version of this really shines. Both are great!

Pours a light gold color with a spicey honey nose. The spice comes through in the flavor with a subdued sweetness and an earthy finish. A very slight alcohol burn at the end. Not bad, but this Meadery has many better offerings.
Pours a hazy gold with a citrusy nose with hints of oak and spices. Flavor is similar to the nose with oak, Brett, lemon, and a bit of dunk. Very nice saison.
Pours a dark purple with grape and honey in the nose. Fruity grape flavor with a sticky sweet finish. Very nice blend!
Pours a pale hazy yellow with a nose of lemon zest, sour funk and Brett. Nice sour.
Pours a light yellow with honey maple nose. Slight maple flavor with sweetness from the honey. Very tasty mead!
Pours a hazy orange color with formal notes on the nose. Nice bitterness in the flavor with hints of mango and citrus. Beautiful balanced finish.
Pours light yellow color with a dry fruity nose. Honey and oak comes through with an earthy flavor, but goes down a little harsh. A strong alcohol burn. Not my favorite dry mead.

By far my favorite mead by Superstition so far. Pours an opaque purple color with a nose that smells of a great dessert! Chocolate raspberry notes. Wonderful flavor with a beautiful sweet finish with a slight alcohol burn!
Pours a purple with a sweet grape nose. Very nice Pinot flavor with a sticky sweet finish. Very nice!
Pours a hazy purple color. Definitely a very berry nose with a tart flavor and sweet finish. Very nice mead.

Pours a purple color with a floral grape notes. Ripe grapes are ever predominant in the taste as well as a little honey adding to the sweetness. A slight alcohol burn going down, but so nice. A great mead if you are red wine lover!
Pours a nice gold color. Nose is floral with honey and a little vanilla. Taste off honey, pear and has a slight burn going down from the alcohol. Not a bad mead, just not my favorite.
Pours an amber-copper color. Nose is sweet with notes of honey and agave. Medium body with a combo sweet-tart taste with nice tart finish. Very good mead!

Pours black with a tan head. Nose is smoky with just a hint of chocolate from the cocoa nibs. Taste is amazing as it has not only the smokiness, but more of the chocolate. Very smooth as it goes down with the warmth from the jalapeos present. In my opinion, probably the best beer Wilderness has put up since both bourbon barrel aged barleywines. Cant wait for the barrel aged version of this!

This is a fresh bottle from the 2014 batch. I prefer my Burton aged so this is my impression of it fresh. Pours a copper/orange with a frothy tan head. A hoppy citrusy nose with a hint of oak aged booziness. Has a medium body with a malty backbone and a sweet, sticky finish.

Pours a hazy orange with a thin white head. Very piney and fruity nose that draws you in. Medium bodied, with a perfect balance of malt and bitterness. A great light IPA that I consider a nice session beer.
Big bold hoppy beer with a smooth bitter finish. This is a Stone Flagship beer. It defines the style.
Love the Double Barrel Ale. Pours a clear amber with a nice off-white head. Nice earthy bitter flavor with a clean finish.
Pours orange with a white head. Fruity nose with a hoppy, piney aroma.Very hoppy flavor with a nice malt backbone. Nice, smooth bitter finish. A very nice DIPA.
Pours gold with very slight hints of citrus and pine. A little sweetness with a medium body, with a light bitter finish. Not a bad IPA, but not a stand out either.
Nice hoppy, citrusy and piny nose. Bitter and well balanced pale. Very good session beer.
Pours a dark brown with a thick tan head. Roasted malt notes with a mild chocolate aroma. Tastes similar to the nose with a light, creamy and balanced finish.
beer_name: Speakeasy Black Hand Chocolate Milk Stout

review_blob: Pours a hazy amber color. Citrusy, floral grass notes with a sticky resinous finish. Definitely better than the last batch of Lagunitas Sucks. Very impressed.
A favorite IPA of mine. Pours a copper body with flowery, piney and citrusy aroma. Very smooth and well balanced with a medium palate and a nice finish. A great AIPA!

Pours an orange-ish copper with a thin white head. Citrusy pine notes with a good amount of hops in the nose. Excellent flavor with just a touch of sweetness and a nice bitter clean finish. A beautifully balanced and flavorful beer with a low ABV.
